    <text id="B0373T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell authorizes Jackson to spend $150 to repair a schoolhouse in
                Waynesboro.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac,
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi>. P.
                        Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-05-20">May 20th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The application of <abbr expan="William">Wm</abbr> Echols, forwarded by you on
                    the 3d inst. for assistance in repairing the schoolhouse at Waynesboro has been
                    approved by the <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr> and $150
                    appropriated to that object.</p>

                <p>You will please see that the necessary repairs are made and forward the vouchers
                    for services and materials purchased to this office for payment.</p>

                <p>The vouchers please have receipted in blank, and forward the bills on a sheet of
                    paper.</p>

                <p>Send them in (if possible) before the end of next month.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Veterans' Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr> Sub <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
